I stopped in here with a buddy of mine after golf for lunch, and we both really liked it.  I had a gyro and greek salad, and both were very enjoyable.  I loved the taziki sauce. (I think thats right).  As noted is some of the other reviews, it is casual dining.  Plastic plates and all.  I just didn't mind.    Service could be a bit faster, but the food was great.  I'll be going back.

