The specialty at this place is a Italian Beef.  I must say, it was not bad, but I have really had better.    What really helped give the extra star are the french frys.  Perfect!  Really, perfect!  Great flavor, crispy but not crunchy, and not greasy.    The Chicago dogs also help.  I think they are only like $2 each, and pretty damn good.    Definitely worth stoping in if you find yourself in the area.  Just not worth extended travel.

